Given a collection of mobile location updates in the form {anonymous user id, UTC timestamp, estimated location coordinates, location error}, we first preprocess the raw data. The preprocessing encompasses three key steps: 1) filtering to retain only meaningful location updates, 2) association with location updates with category information, and 3) quantization of time into time slots. The specifics of how this is done is dependent on the data source used, and will be explained in more detail when the experiments are described in Section 4.
Once the preprocessed location update data, containing N users, T time slots, and C location categories, is available we construct the possible category set for each user at each time slot
Ωij :={k ∈ [C] | category k appears in the location circle of user i at time slot j.}
